faceoff_positive.comments: I love how practical are these. You have 2 colors in one pen- one more subtle and one more fun. My shade Pink Copper / Cashew is more on a lighter side. I have light skin tone and the Cashew was only about 1 shade darker than my concealer so first I was kinda bummed that it doesn't even show on me. But it gave me nice flush of color. I used it also on a lower lash line and it looked great. I used the Pink Copper in the middle of my lid for pop of sparkle and I must say I love how it looked. Great for easy, every day makeup. The formula is not overly creamy, blends easily and I didn't experience any creasing. I would definitely try more shades of these.
faceoff_positive.headline: Practical and great for every day use

faceoff_negative.comments: If I'm being honest, I have very mixed feelings about this product. The shades I received were "Brazen" and "Radient Rose." Starting off with what I enjoyed about this product: the colors are absolutely beautiful. I found that when I swatched the colors on my hand without blending, the colors were very bold and high coverage. The matte side of the stick was in fact matte and the shimmer was glittery throughout the entire stick. The colors on the caps also weren't deceptive, which I notice a lot in makeup especially. I love lighter looks, so blending out the formula was also very easy. The glitter ended up looking like an eye glitter, which I thought looked nice as well. What I found shocking was the smudge proof formula. Once it dries down, it doesn't move. I tested my swatches under water as well, and they stayed perfectly in tact. I also like adding a red/brown under my eyes for a blushed effect, and these sticks were absolutely perfect for that. Now for the more problematic aspects: this stick was so difficult to control. The shape of the tip itself plus the formula just felt very difficult to work with. Certainly not beginner friendly. I also wish the colors were more pigmented when blended out. While blending out was easy, the result felt slightly underwhelming. Overall, I think more practice would be good with this product. I don't believe it's bad, but it's hard to get used to. I received this product for free from Topbox Marketing for testing and review purposes.
faceoff_negative.headline: Difficult, but still usable
